        "body": "In addition to individual waste reduction, the overall number of waste bins in Reykjavík decreased by 21% from 47,200 in 1998 to 37,311 in 2012. The chart below highlights this trend, showing a peak in 2004 before numbers began to fall. The decline indicates a shift in the city's waste management strategies.",
